# Project Structure and Entry Points

This repository is organized as a learning project for PydanticAI. Key entry points and directories:

- `main.py`: simple launcher or scratchpad
- `code_agent/`: advanced code analysis agent package
  - Entry points: `code_agent/core/agent.py`, `code_agent/ui/runner.py`
  - Config: `code_agent/config/mcp.py`, `code_agent/config/logging.py`
  - Tools: `code_agent/tools/toolkit.py`, `code_agent/tools/analyzer.py`, `code_agent/tools/generator.py`, `code_agent/tools/refactoring.py`
  - Docs: `code_agent/docs/README.md`, `code_agent/README.md`
  - Tests: `code_agent/tests/`
- `tools/`: reusable tools for bash, filesystem, file editing, planning, and code analysis
  - `bash_tool.py`, `filesystem_tools.py`, `file_editing_toolkit.py`, `task_planning_toolkit.py`, `code_agent_toolkit.py`
  - Docs: `tools/README_*.md`
- `examples/`: runnable demos organized by topic
  - `examples/basic/hello_world.py`, `examples/tools/filesystem_tools_example.py`, `examples/code_agent/code_agent_example.py`
- `utils/`: helper utilities (`formatter.py`, `terminal_stream.py`, `check_url.py`)
- `scripts/`: project maintenance scripts (`run_all_checks.py`, `check_circular_deps.py`)
- `tests/`: top-level tests for tools and utils
- `pyproject.toml`: project config (mypy, ruff, scripts)
- `README.md`: overview, installation, quick start

